The paper discusses a new method for simulating human peripheral vision using a generative neural network, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the behavioral validation of the model, which suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. Additionally, the use of a neural network implies a focus on machine learning (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of this method in visual design, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
